LOCUS       SBP_tag                   38 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  Streptavidin-binding peptide (SBP-Tag) — a 38-aa synthetic peptide
            selected by mRNA display that binds streptavidin with nanomolar
            affinity (Kd ~2.5 nM) for mild, single-step affinity purification
            and detection, eluted competitively with biotin..
