                     /synonym="streptavidin binding peptide"
                     /note="Streptavidin-binding peptide (SBP-Tag), 38 aa
                     (MDEKTTGWRGGHVVEGLAGELEQLRARLEHHPQGQREP). Synthetic peptide
                     isolated by mRNA display that binds streptavidin with Kd
                     ~2.5 nM; used for one-step affinity purification with mild
                     competitive elution by biotin. Verified to 100% identity
                     over all 38 residues against PDB 4JO6 chain Z. The peptide
                     binds bivalently, contacting the biotin-binding pockets of
                     two separate streptavidin subunits via an N-terminal HVV
                     motif (residues 12-14) and a C-terminal HPQ motif (residues
                     31-33) bridged by a central alpha-helix (residues 17-28)."
